[MK] case called at 8:12am. 
Defendant Cahleb DJ Noble in court with Attorney Jeffrey J De La Rosa.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Victim rights compliance verified.
Sentencing arguments given by counsel. 

On Count #1, the Court sentences Mr. Noble to:
--serve 30 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Work-Release and Huber privileges; to commence forthwith 
--the Court authorizes transfer of the service of this Jail term to Dane County, however this is conditional on it being served only as it would be served at the Jefferson County Jail; there is not to be any day-reporting or electronic monitoring for service of this Jail term 
--0 days credit for time already served given
--pay costs of $243 plus $200 plus $75 in drug testing fees = $518


On Count #2, the Court sentences Mr. Noble to:
--pay costs of $243 plus $200 = $443

On Count #3, the Court sentences Mr. Noble to:
--pay costs of $243 plus $200 = $443

The Court requires the total amount [$1,404 minus $500 cash bail= $904] to be paid in $30 per month installments commencing on 12/7/16 and on the 7th day of each month thereafter until paid in full; non-payment shall result in a 18 day jail term with Work Release and Huber privileges, consecutive
The Court does not order any drivers license revocation.

[MK] case called at 2:24pm. 
Defendant Cahleb Dj Noble in court with Attorney Jeffrey J De La Rosa.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.
The parties indicate that they are prepared to proceed to Jury Trial as scheduled for this Thursday.  Counsel agree that one day trial length is sufficient. 
The Court notes the age of this case and indicates that it will "bump" another case that is on its calendar so that this case may proceed to trial on Thursday. 
The Court does not intend to carry an additional juror. 
The Court will allow the jurors to take written notes and to ask written questions of the witnesses under Wis. JI Criminal 57. 
The Court will have each party list their potential witnesses during Voir Dire. 
The Court intends to read the substantive jury instructions on the charges during Voir Dire, along with Wis. JI Criminal 140 on the burden of proof and the presumption of innocence.

Attorney De La Rosa gives notice of his objection to the introduction of the field testing, however he acknowledges that he does not have legal authority to cite for this objection. 
The Court indicates that it will allow leeway with counsel in cross-examining the witnesses in regard to the issue that there is not a more definitive test on whether the subject material is a controlled substance as opposed to some other substance that is not otherwise controlled. 
The Court finds, that absent some law indicating that field tests are inheritanly unreliable, that such evidence is not excluded under Statute 907.02.
